                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 543.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-06-27"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 27, 1885</date>.
                            (Received July 13.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 332.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Spanish budget of receipts and
                        expenditures for the fiscal year 1885–’86 has just been passed by the
                        Cortes, and shows a total of estimated expenditures of $179,429,378, and of
                        receipts of $174,502,876. Thinking that some details of these governmental
                        expenses and sources of revenue would be of interest, I have prepared from
                        the lengthy official publication the following abstract:</p>
